elements.title: Heiligen-Geist-Kapelle
elements.contents: ... that the Heiligen-Geist-Kapelle in Bruck, a unique late-Gothic chapel with a star rib vault (pictured), was almost demolished to make room for a highway?

elements.title: Rhodesian Independence Bell
elements.contents: ... that the Rhodesian Independence Bell, a replica of the American Liberty Bell, was inscribed "I toll for justice, civilization and Christianity"?

elements.title: Ryan Pretorius
elements.contents: ... that South African American-football kicker Ryan Pretorius wore cleats two sizes too small at Ohio State to simulate kicking barefoot?

elements.title: Piano Sonata No. 2
elements.contents: ... that although Dmitri Shostakovich initially dismissed his own Piano Sonata No. 2 as a "trifle, something impromptu", he would later consider it his most important piano composition?

elements.title: 1991 Burlington mayoral election
elements.contents: ... that Peter Clavelle did not face either a Republican or a Democratic opponent in the 1991 Burlington mayoral election?

elements.title: María Teresa Sesé
elements.contents: ... that María Teresa Sesé wrote 500 romance novels in her native Spanish, then wrote several books in Basque after studying the language for two years?

elements.title: Usra Hendra Harahap
elements.contents: ... that the current Indonesian ambassador to Nigeria, Usra Hendra Harahap, personally led a rescue operation to free Indonesian crew members taken hostage by pirates in June 2020?
